
## Install into system path ##
It's very easy to install donut detector into the default location

$ python setup.py install


## Custom Install ##
If you don't have system-wide permission to execute the above command, you can 
manually specify the install location. You have a few options.

1. Install as user
$ python setup.py install --user

2. If you maintain a set of python 3rd party libraries in your home directory
$ python setup.py install --home=<dir> # <dir> usually is specified as ~

3. Manually specify location.
$ python setup.py install --prefix=<path>